&lt;h2 id="introduction">Introduction
&lt;/h2>&lt;p>After migrating Typecho to a Docker container, enabling HTTPS caused errors when trying to log into the admin panel. It worked fine over HTTP. Since my previous non-Docker deployment didn&amp;rsquo;t have this issue, I initially suspected a Docker networking problem. At the time, I only needed to make a one-off update, so I just disabled HTTPS, finished the changes, and left it. Now that I&amp;rsquo;m using Typecho again and need to post regularly, it&amp;rsquo;s time to fix it properly.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>